bstituing with θ = 1/n immediatly gives $\mathcal {O}(|\varphi |+ n^4)$.□ Proposition 9. $\mathsf {JVV}$-$\mathcal {B}$ makes $\mathcal {O}(n^4\log n + n^3\log n\log \varepsilon ^{-1})$ SAT queries. The size of the queries is $\mathcal {O}(|\varphi |+n^3)$. Proof. Likewise, we substitute θ and δ by their value. The only difference is that the probabilistic approximate counter now makes $\mathcal {O}(\theta ^{-2}\log n \log \delta ^{-1})$ SAT queries. We get that one call to ApproxCount in the JVV algorithm makes $\mathcal {O}(n^2\log (n)\log ((2n+1)2^{n+2}\varepsilon ^{-1}))$ $=\mathcal {O}(n^2\log n(\log n + (n+2) + \log (\varepsilon ^{-1}))=\mathcal {O}(n^3\log n + n^2\log n \log (\varepsilon ^{-1}))$ calls to a SAT oracle. As JVV makes $\mathcal {O}(n)$ calls to ApproxCount, the total number of queries is $\mathcal {O}(n^4\log n + n^3\log n \log (\varepsilon ^{-1}))$. The size of the queries is $\mathcal {O}(|\varphi |+ \frac{n}{\theta ^2})$, substituing with θ = 1/n immediatly gives $\mathcal {O}(|\varphi |+ n^3)$.□ Table 3: Experimental Results. Benchmark Variables Clauses JVV (ɛ = 0.3) $\mathsf {UniGen4}$ (ɛ = 0.3) time (sec/sample) success rate time (sec/sample) success rate s27_new_3_2 17 31 0.38 0.372 0.02 1.00 s27_new_7_4 17 35 0.38 0.372 0.02 1.00 4step 165 418 timeout - 1.03 0.21 s420_15_7 366 994 timeout - 1.56 0.29 GuidanceService2.sk 715 2181 timeout - 1.00 0.23 min-6s 839 2762 timeout - 34.18 0.20 GuidanceService.sk 988 3088 timeout - 1.06 0.29 prod-2s 1113 4974 timeout - 6.91 0.19 90-16-2-q 1216 1920 timeout - 3254.91 0.31 UserServiceImpl.sk 1509 5009 timeout - 0.72 0.29 PhaseService.sk 1686 5655 timeout - 1.39 0.21 ProjectService3.sk 3175 11019 timeout - 6.90 0.19 blasted_case104 3666 11589 timeout - 319.88 0.32 blasted_squaring41 4185 13599 timeout - 3348.58 0.55 ProcessBean.sk 4768 14458 timeout - 5.87 0.23 doublyLinkedList.sk 6890 26918 timeout - 6.28 0.20 01B-1 9159 39959 timeout - 345.59 0.29 107.sk_3_90 8948 40147 timeout - 7.51 0.32 LoginSer